this one will forever hold a special place in my heart. thank you @edogdowning @patrickharpin for taking a chance on me, and giving me one the most humbling and fulfilling experiences of my artistic journey. this show was an incredible undertaking, and to see it have its debut is beyond words. 
.
this crew is the real deal, and am so thankful for the chance to have worked with a team so dedicated and so nurturing. working with this crew showed me the true value of putting your heart into what you do-  great things come from loving what you do, and taking care of the people around you🙏🏽
.
hope you all enjoy watching this as much as we enjoyed making it! #mydadthebountyhunter #netflix

MY DAD THE BOUNTY HUNTER IS LIVE!!! hope you all enjoy what we have in store!!! directing for the first time was an unforgettable experience on this show, i can’t wait to share more work with you all soon🙏🏽
.
funny story, Lisa and Sean’s victory dance is based on how me and @edogdowning greeted each other back in our dreamworks days☕️ it’s hilarious to see how far that’s come🤣

this was the very first sequence i storyboarded on #mydadthebountyhunter back in 2020! 
.
affectionately named ‘the stranger’ @patrickharpin and @edogdowning just said “make sure this guy is f*kin creepy” and let me run with it. 
.
@gustavo_cosio cosio was KILLING IT boarding the cold open, so i tried to juxtapose that dynamic chase with this locked off close encounter. Gus was the best board partner i could have asked for- lightning fast, clean as hell, and always elevated every idea off the page. if a rising tide lifts all boats, Gus is a goddamn tsunami!
.
i’m so proud of the groundwork we laid for this show storyboarding the first 2 episodes- i’m so grateful I got to help Pat and Ev get this crazy concept off the ground, and be a part their passion project. also shoutout to @kenji_ono_udidnt for being an amazing supervising director, and helping this scene across the finish line 🤜🏽🤛🏽

the bathroom brawl in Bucky’s in episode 2 for #mydadthebountyhunter was such a fun assignment🐔 
.
developing a visual style is fraught with unseen creative problems- in this case, what does fighting look like in this ‘world’? how do you tow the line between violent and kid-friendly while staying grounded in the stakes? how would a chicken fight if it had arms? it was a fun challenge to say the least! 
.
film reference always comes in handy! i watched a lot of long lens fight scenes from the bourne series as well as the bathroom fight in MI:fallout for early inspiration 
.
shoutout to @pixiepunch @kenji_ono_udidnt for helping me tie this one down🤜🏽🤛🏽

this chase sequence through pulga in episode 4 of #mydadthebountyhunter had everything in it! high speed moog chases, parkour, flying… it was a tall order, but my board team delivered that frenetic energy from start to finish. we treated it like a relay handing off one section to another, and keeping the plates spinning the whole time was a fun challenge! I started the scene off into the market, @mikejmoloney took the moon chase and sean’s parkour section, and @gustavo_cosio ran anchor through the end of the scene. shoutout to @patrickharpin for writing such a quirky/ dynamic episode for us to sink our teeth into!
.
this was my first time directing, and @patrickharpin & @edogdowning put their full faith in me every step. i am forever grateful for their friendship and leadership throughout the entire production- it was a gamble, but i knew i wasn’t going to let you down! 😅
.
to my incredible board team @mikejmoloney & @gustavo_cosio the A-team aka team chaos magic✨ the bond we formed on this show is something i deeply cherish. i want to thank my brothers for elevating everyone around them with their stellar work ethic, pushing through tough notes and deadlines with humility and positive attitudes, and pushing themselves (and me) to dig deeper every single day. a leader is nothing without trust in their team, and i honestly couldn’t have asked for a better one⚔️
.
and to my brother from another mother @kenji_ono_udidnt thank you for your patience and guidance as our supervising director. every ship needs a captain, and i speak for our megazord of directors @vicehii @akirateku @mrvinceaparo when I say that you brought the best out of us in the most supportive, compassionate, punny way possible. thank you for teaching us about diligence and the importance of a 401k 🤣

i loved boarding anything involving glorlox on #mydadthebountyhunter 🐙
.
I remember laughing out loud at this moment in the episode 2 script, and i asked @patrickharpin @edogdowning ‘we’re going to CUT TO A COMMERCIAL??’☠️ that was definitely a moment i knew this show was something different. I mentioned those Larry H Parker commercials I saw growing up and that was all I had to say lol. also, probably the quickest turnaround of any scene I boarded on the show, and we never touched it after the first pass. if you ever need an intentionally cheap commercial, give me a call at 1(800)BROKLOX 🤣

i worked on #nimona when it was being developed at bluesky studios. it was a different movie back then, but a good amount of that version remained in the final film. one big difference was goldenloin’s character design and his relationship to the director- he was more of an ignorant poster child of the institute. he is a much more sympathetic character in the film and I loved @eugeneleeyang as a much more sympathetic goldenloin 🦁 #storyboards #animatic #blueskystudiosforever

i was working on the first sketch while on a work call, and while i was eyeing these two from a couple tables over they noticed me drawing them. on their way out they stopped by, looked over my shoulder, and asked what i do for work. without thinking i simply said ‘i’m an animator’. @mrvinceaparo was still on the call when i said that and yelled ‘NO YOU’RE NOT!’ 🤣 friends keep you honest… 
.
.
who else has said ‘animator’ to a friend/ stranger/ relative just avoid explaining🤷🏽‍♂️ (some of my uncles still think i ‘animated’ minions, and that’s just what it is now) #gesturedrawing #characterdesign #sketchbook #clipbort

INVINCIBLE SEASON 2 IS HERE!!! working on #invincible was one of the best experiences of my career because of these people right here- thank you to my storyboard team for bringing the best of yourselves every day. i’m so proud of the work we did together on this show- not just the product, but the process and trust we had in each other along the way. halo halo fam forever💙

‘peaches…’
.
this was the first scene i storyboarded on the #blueeyesamurai pilot ‘hammerscale’. this is also my first pass which is why the brothel section is a little different. @janewushu told me to make the audience feel how Ringo would’ve felt in that moment- but I went a little too aggressive😅 #storyboard #animatic #netflix

the Kamo River sequence into the castle is the first time Mizu and Akemi see each other- it’s one of the few moments where eye contact is not foreshadowing conflict or confrontation. @janewushu taught me a ton about lensing and cinematic language on this show⚔️ #blueeyesamurai #storyboard #animatic #netflix

the ‘pig’ scene in #blueeyesamurai was a tough one because it was very static with heavy dialogue- i learned a lot about restraint on this one. it helped that i had @janewushu as my cornerman on this scene PLUS @lingy000 designed the hell out of the set and gave me a beautiful space to shoot #storyboards #animatic #netflix

episode 2 ‘in about six hours i lose my virginity to a fish’ was the first episode i directed for #invincible (sound on 🔊)
.
i was most excited to explore the trauma left behind from season 1. especially since there is a lot going on tonally throughout episode 2, this is the first scene i storyboarded to find the tonal center of amidst everything else going on. shoutout to @danduncanart for supporting me fully throughout the show, @shaunphonso for keeping story in the loop w design and cinematic ideas, and of course my story team for plussing the hell out of everything every step of the way. #storyboard #animatic @invincible.hq  @invincibletv

this is the cold open for season2 ep202 of invincible 🌋
.
these are some of the roughest storyboards I’ve ever done😅but somehow the whole team was able to make sense of it and really make it sing! I learned so much just in my first couple scenes getting my bearings on the style and tone of the show. it was fun to board up to the iconic title card AND to Reginald Vel Johnson’s amazing line reads- I just wish i cleaned up his poses to look more like him.. shoutout to @danduncanart for being patient w my scribbles and also for the only on-model drawings in this board 😅🙏🏽 #invincible #storyboard #animatic #amazon @invincible.hq  @invincibletv

i don’t post my sketches as much as i used to- but im still drawing! im actually kind of glad i don’t feel the pressure to share artwork like i have in the past, and personally it’s been very freeing…
.
that being said, i‘ve officially started scanning drawings for my ‘sketchy book’ series- volume 4🕺🏽 it’ll be a hardcover book w sketches from the past few years, thoughts on drawing from observation, and maybe even some exercises to think about while sketching/designing characters. i’m hoping to have it done by the summer, and ready for @lightboxexpo next year🤞🏽i guess I’ve made my first official resolution for 2024
.
#gesturedrawing #characterdesign #sketchbook #sketchybookvolume4
